Rating: 4
I make this regularly, from October thru March. I follow the recipe with the following changes: apples are shredded instead of chopped, skip the sugar altogether, use sweetened dried cranberries or a dried apple/cranberry mix in lieu of the raisins and add a dollop of vanilla. I'm not keen on yogourt so I skipped that .. and couldn't be bothered to do the nuts. It's delicious and keeps well in the fridge for a few days. I re-warm in the microwave with skim milk and fruit == breakfast!

