I agree it is better using a good quality irish oatmeal (steel cut). I use half milk, half water. Then add 50% more water and same amount of Trader Joes all fruit dried trail mix (bananas, mangoes, cranberries, variousraisins). I have made this twice for a camping crowd and served it with extra milk, brown sugar or honey, cinnamon, crushed pecans to taste and not one camper said they missed their traditional greasy fried breakfast.

Rating: 4
I eat oatmeal for breakfast almost every morning but I was getting a bit bored and thought I'd see what Epicurious had to offer. Wow! I love that this is so healthy but tastes decadent. Sometimes I have it for breakfast and then at the end of the day as desert. I definitely recommend heartier oats (quick oats are great, if you're hanging wallpaper :). I don't bother candying the nuts, I use toasted pecans. I doubt I'll ever make regular oatmeal again.

